                    <Paragraph>
                        <Italic>Explanation of example</Italic> -
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 1: clears all of the sql parameters for the next sql command to execute.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 2: adds the sqlParmFirstName parameter that is defined in SQL Parms tab.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 3: executes sqlCmdUpdate that is defined in SQL Cmds tab.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 4: displays the ReturnCode, which indicates the number of rows affected, if there are no errors; otherwise, it displays a negative error code.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 5: clears all of the sql parameters for the next sql command to execute.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 6: executes the sqlCmdSelect that is defined in the SQL Cmds tab.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 7: sets the row index for arySqlResult.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 8: sets the column index to -1, which causes all columns to be used.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 9: sets all of the children elements under the parent object myColumns to the third row of arySqlResult.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 10: displays the child element name whose parent is myColumns. This displays the column that we updated in Statement 3.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 11: executes a scalar command that places the count of the rows in the test_names in the value for the primitive intScalarResult.
                        <LineBreak/> Statement 12: displays the value for the primitive intScalarResult.
                        <LineBreak/>
                    </Paragraph>
