            <Paragraph>
                <Bold FontSize="24">Columns:</Bold>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                <Bold>ExecuteSQLScalarCommand</Bold> - ExecuteSQLScalarCommand is used to execute a SQL Scalar Command that only returns a single column as the result.  Entity1 is the name of a SQL Command that has been defined in the SQL Cmds tab. Entity2 is primitive that will contain the value of the column that was returned from the scalar query. Here are the columns:
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        1. Sequence
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Sequence is a decimal number with 4 digits after the decimal. It can be modified to allow you to insert rows anywhere in your script. Rows are executed in sequence number order.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph FontSize="14pt" >
                <Italic>
                    <Bold>
                        2. Verb
                    </Bold>
                </Italic>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                ExecuteSQLScalarCommand
            </Paragraph>


